testmd

Class PermutationResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • testmd.PermutationResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<PermutationResult>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PermutationResult.Failed, PermutationResult.Invalid, PermutationResult.Valid

    public abstract class PermutationResult
extends Object
implements Comparable<PermutationResult>
    Contains the results of a just ran or a previously ran Permutation. Parameters, results, notes, etc. are all stored sorted to avoid writing them in random/changing orders. Actual instances created will be PermutationResult.Verified and PermutationResult.Unverified and PermutationResult.Invalid

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  PermutationResult.Failed
      Result for permutations that failed validation.
      static class  PermutationResult.Invalid
      Results for permutations that are invalid and should be skipped.
      static class  PermutationResult.Unverified
      Result for permutations that are valid but cannot be verified.
      protected static class  PermutationResult.Valid
      Base class for all Valid results.
      static class  PermutationResult.Verified
      Result for permutations that were successfully verified, either because the Verification logic passed or the results were unchanged since the last verification.
